Purpose: Generate short, vibe-driven videos to respond to client inquiries, showing a website mockup or explaining how YeahBuddy captures their brand’s essence. These will feel personal and local, with a Kiwi accent and your cheeky tone.

Tool Setup:

  • Platform: Cloud-based web app hosted on Vercel (free tier), using GitHub for version control, as you’ve liked GitHub-based solutions before.
  • Tech Stack:
    • Vercel: Hosts a simple form where you input client details (name, business type, vibe).
    • Puppeteer: Captures screenshots or recordings of a YeahBuddy template or client’s existing site.
    • ElevenLabs TTS (Free Tier): Creates a Kiwi-accented voiceover for that authentic “bud” feel.
    • FFmpeg: Combines visuals and audio into a 30-60 second video.
    • Monday Integration: Automatically log the client’s details and video link in a Monday board (e.g., “Client Responses”) using Monday’s API or Zapier.
  • Workflow:
    1. In Monday, add a client to a “New Inquiries” board with their name, business type, and vibe (e.g., “Jo’s Bakery, cosy, budget-conscious”).
    2. Open the Vercel app (linked via a Monday automation or bookmark) and pull client details from Monday.
    3. Input a short script (or use a pre-saved YeahBuddy template).
    4. The app generates a video, uploads it to Google Drive (free), and logs the link back in Monday.
    5. Send the video link to the client via email or Monday’s email integration.
  • Sample Video Script:

    “Kia ora [Client Name]! It’s your mates at YeahBuddy.nz, pumped to bring [Business Name] online. We’ve caught your [Client Vibe, e.g., ‘chill surf shop energy’] and reckon we can make a website that’s true to your hustle. Here’s a quick look at what we’re thinking—fast, fresh, and all about you. Give us a bell at [Your Phone] or flick an email to yarn more. Chur!”

Monday Integration:

  • Use Monday’s automation to trigger a task when a new inquiry lands (e.g., “Create video for Jo’s Bakery”).
  • Zapier can connect Vercel to Monday, logging the video link in the client’s board.
  • Alternatively, manually copy-paste client details from Monday to the Vercel app (takes 1 min).

Why It’s Quick:

  • ~5 mins to generate a video, reusable for multiple clients.
  • Monday keeps all client info in one place, reducing back-and-forth.
  • Free tools (Vercel, ElevenLabs free tier, Google Drive) keep costs at zero.

Setup Steps:

  1. Fork a GitHub repo with a Vercel/Puppeteer setup (I can recommend one or provide a setup guide).
  2. Sign up for ElevenLabs free tier and add a Kiwi voice.
  3. Set up a Monday board for “Client Responses” with columns: Name, Business Type, Vibe, Video Link.
  4. Use Zapier (free tier) to link Vercel outputs to Monday, or manually log links.

Proposed Tool: Automated Website Walkthrough Recorder

Purpose: Automatically generate a silent, 30-60 second screen recording of a client’s tailored website, simulating a user clicking through key pages (e.g., homepage, about, services, contact). The video acts as a pitch to show clients what YeahBuddy built for them, hosted on a shareable link for easy delivery.

Tool Setup:

  • Platform: Cloud-based web app hosted on Vercel (free tier), using GitHub for version control to keep it low-maintenance and aligned with your preference for GitHub-based solutions.
  • Tech Stack:
    • Puppeteer: Navigates the website, simulates clicks, and captures a screen recording.
    • FFmpeg: Processes the recording into a polished MP4 video.
    • Vercel: Hosts a simple form to input the website URL and select pages to showcase.
    • Google Drive: Stores the video and generates a shareable link (free).
    • Monday Integration: Pulls client website URLs from the Monday “Leads” board and logs the video link back for easy tracking.
  • Workflow:
    1. In Monday’s “Leads” board, select a client (e.g., “Jo’s Bakery”) with their tailored website URL (e.g., a YeahBuddy staging link like jo-bakery.yeahbuddy.nz).
    2. Open the Vercel app (via a Monday automation or bookmark) and input the URL and key pages to record (e.g., homepage, menu, contact).
    3. Puppeteer loads the site, clicks through the selected pages (e.g., 10 seconds per page), and records the screen.
    4. FFmpeg trims and formats the video (30-60 seconds, silent, MP4).
    5. The video uploads to Google Drive, and the shareable link is logged back in Monday.
    6. Send the video link to the client via Monday’s email integration or a templated email, directing them to www.yeahbuddy.nz to choose pricing and go live.

Sample Video Output:

  • A silent, 45-second MP4 showing:
    • Homepage (10s): Scrolls to highlight the hero section and branding.
    • Services/Menu (10s): Clicks a menu item or service to show details.
    • About (10s): Scrolls through the client’s story or vibe.
    • Contact (10s): Highlights the contact form or details.
    • YeahBuddy Branding (5s): Ends with a simple text overlay (e.g., “Made by YeahBuddy.nz”).
  • Hosted on Google Drive with a link like drive.google.com/file/jos-bakery-walkthrough.

Monday Integration:

  • Input: Pull the client’s website URL from the “Leads” board (e.g., a column called “Website URL”).
  • Output: Log the video link in a “Video Link” column and trigger a Monday automation (e.g., “When video link added, send email to client”).
  • Automation: Use Monday’s native integrations or Zapier (free tier) to connect Vercel to Monday, syncing the video link back to the client’s record.

Is Google Drive Paid?

Google Drive offers 15 GB of free storage with every Google account, shared across Drive, Gmail, and Google Photos. This is enough for most small businesses, especially for your use case of storing short, silent MP4 videos (30-60 seconds, ~10-50 MB each). You don’t need to pay for Google Drive unless you exceed 15 GB, which would take hundreds of videos. Paid plans (Google One) start at $1.99/month for 100 GB if you ever need more. Since you’re aiming for free, the 15 GB free tier should work fine for now, and you can manage storage by deleting old videos or using multiple free Google accounts if needed.

Keeping the Walkthrough Tool Free

The tool I proposed uses free tools to automate website click-throughs and screen recordings, ensuring no costs while meeting your needs. Here’s how we keep it free:

  • Vercel: Free tier supports hosting the web app for your scale (unlimited API calls for small projects).
  • Puppeteer: Free, open-source library for browser automation and screen recording.
  • FFmpeg: Free, open-source tool for video processing.
  • Google Drive: Free 15 GB storage for video uploads and shareable links.
  • Monday.com: You’re already using it, so no extra cost. We’ll use free automations or Zapier’s free tier for integration.
  • No Audio: Skipping voiceovers (e.g., ElevenLabs) keeps it simpler and avoids API costs.
